ir shave or trim facial hair and give enemas the surgeon came with the army at war but could be used by individuals in peacetime the surname bader comes from german and jewish ashkenazic origins and refers to the occupation of barber surgeon barber or one who tends a bath house the german verb baden means to bathe but when capitalized the surname baden is a geographical surname referring to the region of badenwürttemberg in germany see alsoedit feldsher elinor sneshell further readingedit gross dominik arnold schlegel – and the agony of the barbersurgeons as a profession gesnerus – swiss journal of the history of medicine and sciences   pp – gross dominik marriage strategies social prestige and property of barbersurgeons in thcentury württemberg an evaluation of marriage and probate inventories historical social research   pp – dobson jesse milnes walker r barbers and barbersurgeons of london a history of the barbers and barbersurgeons companies oxford  referencesedit  a b c d e mcgrew roderick  encyclopedia of medical history new york mcgraw hill pp – isbn     henry viii c   sven med tidskr  from barber to surgeon the process of professionalization svensk medicinhistorisk tidskrift   – pmid    gangs of new york dir martin scorsese perfs leonardo dicaprio cameron diaz and daniel daylewis miramax  dvd scene at timestamp   upplandiase en webbplats om uppland  begrepp yrken  titlar upplandiase  february  archived from the original on  september  retrieved  september    the origins and meaning of ashkenazic last names wwwjewishcurrentsorg retrieved    bader name meaning  bader family history at ancestrycom ancestrycom   surname database baden last name origin the internet surname database   dictcc  baden  wörterbuch englischdeutsch dictcc  external linksedit media related to barber surgeon at wikimedia commons authority control gnd  retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlebarbersurgeonoldid categories medieval occupationshistory of surgerytraditional healthcare 